EP  - 174
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Von Neumann-Morgenstern preferences over terminal consumption can be inferred from wealth on a single sample path when markets are complete and returns follow a known law in a neo-classical investment problem in either a discrete-time i.i.d. binomial model or a continuous-time diffusion model with a Gaussian state variable. Numerical results suggest that useful information about preferences can be obtained from even a single noisy sample of monthly observations of a portfolio over 5 years.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/10.1.151
ER  - 



